idden=\"hidden\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Most bees are relatively small, with an average length of 0.5-2 cm, depending on their type. However, some species can grow up to 3 cm long.<\/span><\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-mobile-title\" aria-selected=\"false\" data-tab=\"3\" role=\"tab\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-5043\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Description<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-5043\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"3\" role=\"tabpanel\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-5043\" tabindex=\"0\" hidden=\"hidden\"><p style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Bees are fascinating insects that belong to the family Apidae. They are known for their role in the pollination and production of honey. Bees play a vital role in the ecosystem by collecting pollen and nectar from flowers. They also help to pollinate plants, which in turn helps to provide food for other animals.<\/span><\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-f4790ff\" data-id=\"f4790ff\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-5aaa333\" data-id=\"5aaa333\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ddf938e elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"ddf938e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div cl